Representation of Santa Around the World

images.description:
Background:
George Takei, best known for playing Sulu on the original Star Trek, was in the internment camp from when he was five years old. As a child he spent four years in the internment camp. 

--

Reading George Takei's post I wondered how Santa is represented around the world. Is it purely the Coca-Cola Santa? 

Now, I had no idea if the bot is correct or not. I tried to check the images from the bot for correctness by searching on Google/Bing/Getty-Images/Flickr for Santa images from that location. Do note sampling bias in search results. Search results also had quite a few fake beards, so the bot images look closer to idealisms.

Please weigh-in.

Papua New Guinea 

To verify if the bot is correct, I tried searching Google/Bing/GettyImages/Flickr. I can locate very-few images of Santa in Papua New Guinea so I assume the bot is purely imagining the images for Papua New Guinea, e.g.: "what if a person from Papua New Guinea looked like Santa".

Norway

Matches pretty well with search engine results.

images.description:
Hello everyone, long time lurker here on an alt account, first ever public post on either accounts. I don’t know why I had the idea to post this on here when I’m honestly not that big into posting very personal details about my private life onto social media. Hell, I deleted FB right after I graduated high school for that very reason. I now only use sites like Twitter, Instagram and imgur to look at fan art, follow said artists/YouTubers I like, gaming news, and memes. But here I am, about posting a short dialogue about my life for reasons I can’t explain.

Earlier this month, my father, after a history of things I do not wish to get into, had enough of my “disrespect” and gave me till the end of the month to “get the fuck out of his house" (my father and I do not get along anymore. Long story obvious, he doesn’t like it when people refuse to let him control them. If I did anything he deemed “disrespectful” I would be yelled at. Unlucky for him, for the past 4 years, I have been secretly recording any and all conversations between us and keeping the ones where he looses his temper and violently lashes out at me or my mother and brother as proof in case the day comes where he eventually crosses THE line. Anyways, with less than 15 days, I spent every hour of every day searching for a cheap place that my friend and I could stay in for a time being as we were already planning on moving out of state sometime next year. Cut to today. 
December 26th, 2022, after numerous rejections, I was blessed to find a phenomenal deal on a 6 month lease for a 2 bedroom apartment my my friend, myself and my cat. Everything has been signed and paid for and I’m currently typing this all up in my vacant room on my iPad as I wait for my friend to arrive with the U-haul so I can start loading my furniture and finally be free from my abusive father. 

To say these last couple of weeks have been stressful would be an understatement. I have barely been able to eat, My sleep schedule has gotten out of control. And I have been fighting off numerous panic/anxiety attacks. But today is when that all finally comes to an end and I can finally be free from all that stress.

I had originally intended to move out a couple of years ago with my best friend (who is moving out with me right now) but the pandemic put a stop to those plans. Things were going fine until I lost my job and had to drop out of school due to my mental health and from a serious lack of medication (lost insurance and was off ADHD meds for nearly half a year). I was unemployed for over 12 months, thankfully found a job (before I quit because they refused to give me more hours), my friend got me a job at his work (then accidentally quit that place because of a stupid panic decision I regretted but at the same time was glad I made) then a few months later got a job delivering pizzas that I kept from Jan of 2022 all the way to the beginning of Oct 2022. I say that because I have been on an extended “medical leave” from work due to my doctor suspecting I have some form of epilepsy. Despite the restrictions placed on me, I am still looking for work so I can replenish my saving after buying a car, putting money down on the apartment, and buying new furniture. 

Now, I know things are not going to just suddenly change for the better over night. I have a history or mental health issues (all thanks to my father and his 26 years of abuse) and I have already scheduled a meeting with a counselor that specializes in adults dealing with trauma from their childhood. It will be a long journey to find the peace I need in my life. But just having a place to call “my own” where I no longer have to worry about my father and his temper, or be free from the place where so much painful and traumatic memories transpired is more than a big enough first step. 

Tldr: abusive father kicked me out. Found a place. Cutting off all contact with him and absolutely do not plan to ever reconnect to forgive him in the future. The things he has done to our family are unforgivable. So please, don’t comment anything like that.

I heard her talking in her room and knocked and went in to tell her lights out, she was wearing a santa hat and had put one on the urn, cradled in her lap. She just looked at me and I said I was sorry and left her to it. 

I sobbed in the kitchen for 20 minutes before I could pull myself back together and keep wrapping gifts from "santa".

My daughter's x-mas is even tougher than mine.

Edit: I'm in my last year for being licensed as a clinical mental health counselor, and I've been seen a grief counselor since she died. Finally found a teen grief counselor (took waaaay longer than it should, our healthcare system in the US is garbage) and my daughter is seeing her once a week.  

Yes, I've retained a malpractice attorney. It was a nightmare beyond anything I've ever seen in a tv show or movie. I will not tell the story here. I lied to the rest of the family and told them she passed away peacefully at the hospital. It made no sense telling them what really happened.

Also, make a will if you haven't. Probate court is a nightmare in the US. Seriously, it's bad, really bad, far worse than you realize. My ex didn't have one and I have to go to court, pay thousands to attorneys, just to make sure my daughter gets what is already hers. It. Make. No. Sense.

Thank you to everyone for the kind words and thoughts.
Sorry to have bummed everyone out :/

images.description: Left an abusive relationship last year. Worked retail for the last 20 years. 36 and happy finally. Sorry so late. But family and friends had my attention for once. Also, I have a 16months old! I’m so happy! I work at a winery now as family. Never once did I ever think I would work a job that when they said family they meant it.

Cynane (Kee-nah-nay) after Alexander the Great’s half-sister who was trained as a warrior. Hopefully Cynane will grow up big and strong and protect our farm animals (she’s a working dog). 

In the meantime, I’ve been calling her “Pooper”. It went from ‘Pupper’ to ‘Pooper’ as these things do tend to morph. “Pooper” is an absolute monster! Don’t let this cute sleeping form fool you! She’s a slipper nabbing thief! She has a weird dislike for the vacuum hose, and she seems angry at my socked feet for taking off in MY slippers. The audacity! How dare they?!

Sleeping in the day because she likes to stay up all night howling and barking to make sure we are well informed that bedtime at night is torture and against her nature. As is being taken on a leash to potty because frolicking at 3:00am in the freezing ass weather is the very definition of this doggo’s joy. She will hold her poops for in the house if she’s leashed outside. Apparently she needs freedom and privacy to poo… unless it’s in the house then she’ll unapologetically squat right in front of you.

Half seal half polar bear? She looks like she’s Saoirse from Song of the Sea. 

It’s been… twenty two years? since I last owned a puppy…? About that long. So. Much. Energy! And it’s far too cold right now to run and frolic outside to expend said energy. She’s like a toddler running around with sharp knives in her mouth. Into everything, and I’m so sleep deprived! Though we did meet the cow, pig, chickens and ducks the other day and once the weather warms up we’ll transition her to spending more time with the animals she will come to protect once she is big enough.

images.description: This is Volodymyr Ezhov, one of the latest victims of Russia's attempted genocide in Ukraine. Avid fans of the STALKER series may recognize him.

A younger Ezhov's likeness was used as the model for Loki in Call of Pripyat, and he was a member of the dev team for Clear Sky. I haven't played STALKER in a while, and for the unfamiliar it's an amazing series of post apocalypse shooter RPGs, akin to Fallout. The devs from STALKER later went on to make Metro 2033.

RIP to this amazing warrior, a fighter for Freedom, and a part of a beloved series known around the world. All souls return to the zone eventually, STALKER. I hope in the lifetime of his children that his people may find peace.

images.description: Well, it's been another weird, difficult mental health year for me. While I feel like I'm ending it in a less than desirable position, there were some glimmers of an epic life this year too. Some dreams finally fulfilled, some further than they've ever been, people lost and incredible people gained. First picture, a day I felt pretty. Second picture, a day I felt entirely happy, present, not a single worry. Neither happened very often.
Be gentle to yourselves friends, be patient and understanding and keep on keeping on. Merry Christmas if you celebrate it, congratulations on it almost being over if it's a hard time for you. Love xx
